  abstract = {NEW YORK TIMES~BESTSELLER \textbullet{} WINNER OF THE PULITZER PRIZE \textbullet{} One of the most acclaimed books of our time, this modern classic ``has set a new standard for reporting on poverty'' (Barbara Ehrenreich,~The New York Times Book Review).In~Evicted, Princeton sociologist and MacArthur ``Genius'' Matthew Desmond follows eight families in Milwaukee as they each struggle to keep a roof over their heads. Hailed as ``wrenching and revelatory'' (The Nation), ``vivid and unsettling'' (New York Review of Books),~Evicted~transforms our understanding of poverty and economic exploitation while providing fresh ideas for solving one of twenty-first-century America's most devastating problems. Its unforgettable scenes of hope and loss remind us of the centrality of home, without which nothing else is possible.~NAMED ONE OF THE BEST BOOKS OF THE YEAR BY President Barack Obama \textbullet ~The New York Times Book Review~\textbullet ~The Boston Globe~\textbullet ~The Washington Post~\textbullet ~NPR~\textbullet{} Entertainment Weekly~\textbullet ~The New Yorker \textbullet ~Bloomberg~\textbullet ~Esquire~\textbullet{} BuzzFeed \textbullet{} Fortune~\textbullet ~San Francisco Chronicle \textbullet ~Milwaukee Journal Sentinel~\textbullet ~St. Louis Post-Dispatch~\textbullet ~Politico~\textbullet ~The Week~\textbullet ~Chicago Public Library~\textbullet ~BookPage~\textbullet ~Kirkus Reviews~\textbullet ~Library Journal~\textbullet ~ Publishers Weekly~\textbullet{} Booklist \textbullet ~Shelf AwarenessWINNER OF:~The National Book Critics Circle Award for Nonfiction \textbullet{} The PEN/John Kenneth Galbraith Award for Nonfiction \textbullet{} The Andrew Carnegie Medal for Excellence in Nonfiction \textbullet{} The Hillman Prize for Book Journalism \textbullet{} The PEN/New England Award \textbullet{} The~Chicago Tribune~Heartland PrizeFINALIST FOR THE~LOS ANGELES TIMES~BOOK PRIZE AND THE KIRKUS PRIZE``Evicted~stands among the very best of the social justice books.''\textemdash Ann Patchett, author of~Bel Canto~and~Commonwealth~``Gripping and moving\textemdash tragic, too.''\textemdash Jesmyn Ward, author of~Salvage the Bones ``Evicted~is that rare work that has something genuinely new to say about poverty.''\textemdash San Francisco Chronicle},
